    "# Two Moons"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "<div class=\"btn btn-notebook\" role=\"button\">\n",

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "fnXS_blOmCWp"
   },
   "source": [
    "The following example is a binary classification domain adaptation issue. The goal is to learn the classification task on the target data (black points) knowing only the labels on the source data (red and blue points).\n",
    "\n",
    "The following methods are being tested:\n",
    "\n",
    "- [Source Only](#Source-Only)\n",
    "- [DANN](#DANN)\n",
    "- [ADDA](#ADDA)\n",
    "- [Deep CORAL](#DeepCORAL)\n",
    "- [mSDA](#mSDA)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "RLzLSvFQmCWq"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "\n",
    "import adapt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import tensorflow as tf\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import OneHotEncoder\n",
    "from sklearn.decomposition import PCA\n",
    "from sklearn.manifold import TSNE\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score\n",
    "from sklearn.datasets import make_moons\n",
    "\n",
    "from tensorflow.keras import Model, Sequential\n",
    "from tensorflow.keras.optimizers import Adam, SGD, RMSprop, Adagrad\n",
    "from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense, Input, Dropout, Conv2D, MaxPooling2D, Flatten, Reshape, GaussianNoise, BatchNormalization\n",
    "from tensorflow.keras.constraints import MinMaxNorm\n",
    "from tensorflow.keras.regularizers import l2\n",
    "\n",
    "from adapt.feature_based import DANN, ADDA, mSDA, DeepCORAL"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "m6-fzSsMmCWr"
   },
   "source": [
    "## Setup"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "PBSIhTrqmCWr"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def make_moons_da(n_samples=100, rotation=30, noise=0.05, random_state=0):\n",
    "    Xs, ys = make_moons(n_samples=n_samples,\n",
    "                        noise=noise,\n",
    "                        random_state=random_state)\n",
    "    Xs[:, 0] -= 0.5\n",
    "    theta = np.radians(-rotation)\n",
    "    cos_theta, sin_theta = np.cos(theta), np.sin(theta)\n",
    "    rot_matrix = np.array(\n",
    "        ((cos_theta, -sin_theta),\n",
    "         (sin_theta, cos_theta))\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    Xt = Xs.dot(rot_matrix)\n",
    "    yt = ys\n",
    "    return Xs, ys, Xt, yt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "colab": {
     "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
     "height": 319
    },
    "executionInfo": {
     "elapsed": 466,
     "status": "ok",
     "timestamp": 1631091095535,
     "user": {

     "nbsphinx-thumbnail"

   "outputs": [

     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x360 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"

     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "Xs, ys, Xt, yt = make_moons_da()\n",
    "\n",
    "x_min, y_min = np.min([Xs.min(0), Xt.min(0)], 0)\n",
    "x_max, y_max = np.max([Xs.max(0), Xt.max(0)], 0)\n",
    "x_grid, y_grid = np.meshgrid(np.linspace(x_min-0.1, x_max+0.1, 100),\n",
    "                             np.linspace(y_min-0.1, y_max+0.1, 100))\n",
    "X_grid = np.stack([x_grid.ravel(), y_grid.ravel()], -1)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax1 = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(6, 5))\n",
    "ax1.set_title(\"Input space\")\n",
    "ax1.scatter(Xs[ys==0, 0], Xs[ys==0, 1], label=\"source\", edgecolors='k', c=\"red\")\n",
    "ax1.scatter(Xs[ys==1, 0], Xs[ys==1, 1], label=\"source\", edgecolors='k', c=\"blue\")\n",
    "ax1.scatter(Xt[:, 0], Xt[:, 1], label=\"target\", edgecolors='k', c=\"black\")\n",
    "ax1.legend(loc=\"lower right\")\n",
    "ax1.set_yticklabels([])\n",
    "ax1.set_xticklabels([])\n",
    "ax1.tick_params(direction ='in')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "8f7EdGLqmCWt"
   },
   "source": [
    "## Network"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "0UinmP-tmCWt"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def get_task():\n",
    "    model = Sequential()\n",
    "    model.add(Flatten())\n",
    "    model.add(Dense(10, activation=\"relu\"))\n",
    "    model.add(Dense(10, activation=\"relu\"))\n",
    "    model.add(Dense(1, activation=\"sigmoid\"))\n",
    "    return model"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "MB6Lo7FzmCWu"
   },
   "source": [
    "<a name=\"Source-Only\"></a>\n",
    "## Source Only"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "ovAaeZrWmCWu"
   },
   "source": [
    "For source only, we use a DANN instance with lambda set to zero. Thus, the gradient of the discriminator is not back-propagated through the encoder."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "GkQv5L1nmCWv"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "src_only = DANN(task=get_task(), loss=\"bce\", optimizer=Adam(0.001, beta_1=0.5),\n",
    "            copy=True, lambda_=0., metrics=[\"acc\"], gamma=10., random_state=0)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "colab": {
     "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",

   ],
   "source": [
    "src_only.fit(Xs, ys, Xt, yt, epochs=800, batch_size=34, verbose=0);\n",
    "pd.DataFrame(src_only.history_).plot(figsize=(8, 5))\n",
    "plt.title(\"Training history\", fontsize=14); plt.xlabel(\"Epochs\"); plt.ylabel(\"Scores\")\n",
    "plt.legend(ncol=2)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },

   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "yt_pred = src_only.predict(Xt)\n",
    "acc = accuracy_score(yt, yt_pred>0.5)\n",
    "\n",
    "yp_grid = src_only.predict(X_grid).reshape(100, 100)\n",
    "\n",
    "X_pca = np.concatenate((src_only.predict_features(Xs),\n",
    "                        src_only.predict_features(Xt)))\n",
    "X_pca = PCA(2).fit_transform(X_pca)"
   ]
  },
